 cons in one of the most unclear lines in modern theory.} 8. Bd3 {[%csl Ge4][%cal Yd3e4,Yg5e4,Ge5e4] The main line nowadays, and certainly the most challenging continuation for Black. The bishop is awkward on [d3], but it prevents Black from pushing ...[e4] easily, which is very important for these types of positions, as we have seen earlier.} Nd5 {[%cal Gf7f5,Rd8g5] Attacking the knight on [g5] and freeing the way for the f-pawn.} ({This is clearly the main line for Black since, for example,} 8... h6 {can be met by} 9. Ne4 $1 {and White is doing pretty well there, according to theory.}) 9. Ne4 {This is risky in general when Black can push for ...[f5], and this position is no exception.} (9. h4 {This is just a crazy line. White wants to keep the knight on [g5] and then play [Qf3] or [Qh5], which are not so easy to meet. Even taking on [h7] can be an option sometimes.} Be7 10. Qf3 {Now Black can't protect the pawn on [f7], since the bishop is blocking the queen's way, whilst ...[O-O] would just drop the [h7]-pawn. 9...Bd6 Almost a novelty, only played in one game. The idea is to be ready to meet both [Qf3] and [Qh5]. 10.Nc3 A normal developing move, against which the idea of ...[Bd6] can be shown. 10...h6 11.Nge4 Be7 ∞ We want to kick that knight from [e4] and not allow the trade. 10.Qf3 Qe7 This is the difference compared to 9...Be7 lines. Black doesn't have to go for ...[f5] immediately, and enter crazy complications. 11.O-O f5! 12.Bxf5 Rf8 13.Qh5+ g6 14.Bxg6+ hxg6 15.Qxg6+ Kd8 ∞ The game is complicated, but Black has decent chances for some attack on the kingside.}) 9... Nf4 {[%cal Rf4d3,Rf4g2] White has to retreat with the bishop to [f1] if they want to keep the extra pawn.} 10. Bf1 (10. Qf3 $2 f5 {∓ The queen is badly placed on [f3].}) 10... f5 11. Ng3 {Takes away the option of [g3] and attacking the [f4]-knight.} Bd6 $1 {[%cal Ge8g8]} ({In case of} 11... Bc5 {, White could play} 12. c3 {with a potential [d4] tempo.}) 12. Ne2 (12. d4 Qe7 {with a lot of trouble on the e-file.}) 12... Ne6 $1 {Of course, the knight on [e2] is just blocking White's development, so we are not interested in trading it.} 13. d4 Qe7 $17 {[%csl Ye2][%cal Re7e1,Ge8g8,Gf5f4] White has big problems with finishing the development, since the knight can't really move from [e2].} *

