{Welcome to the fourth and last Quickstarter Guide of the course! The main line, the Ruy Lopez, is on the agenda in this chapter. Following the approach of the course, you'll not have to learn main lines after 4...Nf6. The choice of the repertoire is the Deferred Cozio Defense! It doesn't even have an official name; it is just deferred because Black is not going for 3...Nge7, which is the Cozio, but a move later.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 {[%cal Rb5c6,Yf3e5]} ({The Ruy Lopez, the traditional main line against 1...e5. Black has found some reliable defenses, particularly the Berlin, which has driven players to move to} 3. Bc4 {or other lines, but overall, it is still White's No. 1 option. Our opponent continues to put us under pressure; we have just protected the pawn on [e5] with the knight, which is under attack.}) 3... a6 4. Ba4 (4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. O-O Qd6 {is our choice against the Exchange Variation.}) 4... Nge7 {[%cal Ge7g6,Yg6e5,Gd7d5] The move itself will not be such a big surprise for White since, followed by ...[g6], this used to be quite a popular line a decade ago. However, with ...[Ng6], the line is very fresh and has just started to get more popular, so your opponents will most likely not be too well prepared. It is a fighting choice which fits well with the rest of the repertoire and since the goal is to play ...[d5] quickly, it is a good pairing with the Italian chapters. What you can learn about in the following lines:} (4... Nge7 {• A super rare line in the Exchange Variation, where White can very easily get worse early on. • What is an ideal setup for Black in the endgame of the Exchange Variation. • How to quickly finish the development if White goes for} 5. d4 {against the Cozio. • Why it is difficult to play against 5.Nc3 (, and a mysterious 'novelty' one game was played at move 6! for Black. • How to react if White is starting to attack the knight on [g6] as early as 6.h4! • Important move order details in the) 5.c3 Ng6 6.d4 lines.}) (4... Nge7 {• Quickly equalising lines against the very popular} 5. O-O Ng6 6. c3 {variation. • Some early tricks for Black in the main line.}) *

