1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 {[%cal Rb5c6,Yf3e5]} ({The Ruy Lopez, the traditional main line against 1...e5. Black has found some reliable defenses, particularly the Berlin, which has driven players to move to} 3. Bc4 {or other lines, but overall, it is still White's No. 1 option. Our opponent continues to put us under pressure; we have just protected the pawn on [e5] with the knight, which is under attack.}) 3... a6 4. Ba4 Nge7 {[%cal Ge7g6,Yg6e5,Gd7d5]} 5. c3 {[%cal Gd2d4,Yc3d4]} Ng6 {[%csl Ge5][%cal Yg6e5,Gd7d5]} 6. h4 {[%cal Rh4h5] Not very common, but recently, such moves have become very popular in almost all openings, even without a knight on [g6].} Be7 $1 {[%csl Gg5][%cal Yh7h5,Yd2d4,Gf3g5] This is the best move! The inclusion of [h4]-...[h5] before playing [d4] would clearly favour White as our kingside has now been weakened, and the knight can jump to [g5].} 7. h5 (7. g3 h5 $1 {But now ...[h5] is well-timed! We have better development than on the previous move, so we can react aggressively against [d4].} 8. d4 d5 $1 {As usual, if we can play this move, then we are doing great.}) 7... Nf4 $1 {[%cal Rf4d3,Rf4g2]} 8. d4 {A typical pawn sacrifice, but the knight doesn't have to return to [f4].} Nxg2+ 9. Kf1 Nh4 $1 (9... Nf4 10. d5 {± Followed by [Nxe5], and Black is in very bad shape.}) 10. Nxe5 (10. d5 {If the [c6]-knight moves, White takes the pawn on [e5].} Nxf3 11. Qxf3 Na5 $1 {A very important move! Everything else would be rather bad for Black. The knight from [a5] can re-enter the game much more easily than from [b8] or [a7] and also takes away the bishop's [b3]-square.} 12. Rg1 g5 {∞ With a very complicated and unusual position. Even though Black's kingside looks seriously weakened, it is not so easy to attack there after ...[O-O], ...[Kh8],...[f6].}) 10... Nxe5 11. dxe5 b5 12. Bb3 O-O $132 {Black basically has three different ideas for opening the position: playing ...[Kh8] and then ...[f5], going for ...[d6], or playing ...[a5] followed by ...[Ba6]. You can check out quite a few sample lines in the main course.} *

