1. e4 {[%csl Gd5,Ge4][%cal Gd1h5,Gf1c4,Ye4d5] The most popular first move and, in the vast majority of the cases, the choice of the players who are new to the game, since it can lead to open positions and there are many tricks, traps, which are very tempting to try out.} e5 {[%csl Ge4,Ge5] Our choice against 1. [e4]. This is the most classic way to respond to the King's pawn opening since it controls the center in the same way White just did. It is an 'evergreen' opening, as it has been, is, and will always be popular at all levels for its solidity and richness of play.} 2. Bb5 {The Portuguese Opening, not a very popular one, and understandably so. It looks like that White is attacking the shadow of the [c6]-knight.} c6 {Looks like the most logical, and this move questions White's whole concept.} 3. Ba4 d5 {We will have to take back with the queen on [d5], but it is not a problem at all.} 4. exd5 {The most solid move for White.} Qxd5 5. Qf3 (5. Nf3 $4 {This is somewhat inaccurate.} Qe4+ 6. Qe2 Qxa4 {-+}) 5... Nf6 6. Nc3 Qa5 7. Bb3 (7. Nge2 {This is a little bit less precise, because now it will be more difficult to play [Bb3].} Be6 $1 8. O-O Nbd7 {⩱ White can only recapture with the c-pawn in case they want to play [Bb3].}) 7... Nbd7 $15 {[%csl Gb3][%cal Yd7c5,Yc5b3] With the idea of playing ...[Nc5] and taking the bishop on [b3], Black is slightly better in this position. Let's see a few options, how the game can develop.} (7... Nbd7 8. a3 {Providing a retreat square for the bishop.} Bd6 9. Nge2 O-O {And now White is facing a problem, since [O-O] doesn't really work.} 10. Ng3 {( • 10.O-O? Nc5! 11.Ba2 e4! 12.Qe3 Bxh2+ Wins a pawn for Black, because of the ...[Ng4] fork. 13.Kh1 Nb3!! And this wins the game, because of ...[Qh5] coming. 14.Bxb3 Qh5 -+) ( • 10.d3?! A logical attempt to stop ...[e4] ideas and then castle, but for the moment the king is in the pin. 10...e4! 11.dxe4 Ne5 12.Qe3 Bc5 13.Qf4 Ng6 14.Qf3 Bg4 15.Qg3 h5 -+ Not only attempting to trap the queen, but also threatening with ...[Nxe4] since the bishop on [g4] is protected now. )} Nc5 11. Ba2 Ne6 {⩱ The knight is coming to [d4], and Black is comfortably better here.}) *

