 popular move in the position, White stops ...[d5] and we also can't take on [e4] for free.} d6 ({The most ambitious move for Black. Instead,} 8... Bxc3 9. Bxc3 Nxe4 {is also possible, where after} 10. Qf4 Re7 11. Bxf7+ Rxf7 12. Qxe4 {we can get an equal but complicated position.}) 9. Nf3 {This move is protecting on [e4] by tactical means, and looks like a better move than 9. [f3], so will be probably the main line in the future.} Be6 {[%csl Gc4] Continuing the development and trading White's strongest piece, the [c4]-bishop.} (9... Bxc3 $6 10. Bxc3 Nxe4 11. Rhe1 Bf5 {(11...Re7 12.Ne5!)} 12. Qf4 {∞ And White is doing pretty well.}) 10. Bxe6 Rxe6 {[%csl Re4][%cal Rb4c3,Yf6e4,Ye6e4] There are no more tactical tricks connected with the [f7]-square, so the [e4]-pawn is in danger again.} 11. Ng5 {[%csl Ge4][%cal Rg5e6,Gg5e4] Played exclusively in OTB chess, which is not a surprise, it is not only protecting the pawn, but also gains a tempo on the rook.} Re8 {[%csl Re4][%cal Gh7h6] ...[h6] is coming, so the pawn on [e4] is still an issue.} 12. f3 {[%csl Ge4][%cal Gf3e4] Protecting the pawn on [e4] is the most common choice for White.} Ne5 {[%csl Gc4][%cal Re5c4] In the absence of the light-squared bishops, the [c4]-square is a pretty nice target for the knights.} 13. Qe2 h6 {Forcing the knight to an awkward square.} 14. Nh3 (14. h4 $2 {White is correct that we can't take on [g5] yet, but after} Nh5 $1 {-+ Followed by ...[Bxc3], we already can take on [g5], since the pawn will not be protected, unless White wants to play [bxc3] on the queenside, which doesn't look good, to say the least.}) 14... c6 {[%cal Gd6d5,Gb7b5,Ge5c4,Re8e2] Nice improving move, both ...[b5] and ...[d5] because of the X-ray on the queen can be an idea now.} 15. Nf4 a5 {[%cal Yb7b5,Yd6d5,Ga5b4]} 16. h4 d5 $1 {Against the flank attack, we strike in the centre, since we are well-educated about the basic principles! 🙂} 17. exd5 cxd5 $15 {[%cal Rd5d4,Re5c4,Ga8c8] We have threats like ...[d4] or ...[Nc4], but we can also further improve our position by playing ...[Rc8] in the next move, Black is clearly in the driver's seat.} *

