an't keep a clean extra pawn.} Nxd5 13. Qxd5 Bb4+ $1 {This is the problem, the king has to stay in the center.} 14. Bd2 Bxd2+ 15. Kxd2 Qc7 {∓ With moves like ... [Bc6], ...[Rad8] coming, Black has obviously much more than sufficient compensation for the pawn.}) 12... Bg4 $1 {Black is winning back the pawn with a better position.} 13. Qg3 Bxe2 14. Kxe2 {Of course, it shouldn't be good, but White tries to keep the [d5]-pawn.} (14. Nxe2 Nxd5 {∓ A clear advantage with a better structure.}) 14... Bd4 $15 {We have time to recover the pawn on [d5]. Black can continue with ...[Qb6], ...[Rac8] and put more pressure on White.} (14... Nxd5 $2 {Would be an unfortunate tactical error.} 15. Nxd5 Qxd5 16. Bh6 {± White is winning the exchange.}) *

