 [g3] is also misplaced, exposed to ...[Bd6] or ...[Nh5] ideas.}) ({•} 8. d4 $6 {White is trying to speed up the development for the pieces on the queenside, the problem with the move that it fails to keep the extra pawn.} exd4 9. Bg5 Be7 {...[Nxd5] tactics are in the air, because the knight is protecting the bishop on [e7].} 10. Bc4 O-O 11. O-O Nxd5 $1 {Secures a slight edge for Black.} 12. Bxe7 Nxe7 13. cxd4 Bc6 {⩱ White has an IQP, which is well blockaded, there is no active play to compensate for it, so Black can be very optimistic here.}) 8... b5 {A pretty logical try to improve on the main line, which is 8...[e4] and almost exclusively played. The point is that once we play ...[e4], White's queen is going to drop back to [e2] and control the [b5]-square, so we can't insert this move so easily anymore. Eventually, kicking the bishop away from the [a2]-[g8] diagonal can help to regain the pawn on [d5], but even if we just win some space there, it is a good deal for Black.} 9. Bb3 (9. Be2 $6 {Was tried in practice, but doesn't make too much sense.} Bd6 {White can't prevent both ...[e4] and ...[Bg4] so they are already in trouble.} 10. h3 {(10.d3 Bg4 11.Qe3 Nxd5 Black regains the pawn with the space and development advantage. 12.Qg5 Qxg5 13.Bxg5 Be6 ⩱)} e4 $1 11. Qe3 O-O {White's position looks bad, and it is bad. 🙂} 12. c4 Re8 13. O-O c6 {↑ With huge activity for Black. It can be instructive if you try out a few lines for White here, just to see how easily such positions can collapse.}) 9... e4 {Of course! We are not waiting for White to play [d3] and be pretty solid.} 10. Qe2 Bd6 {Continuing normal development, and the bishop is very strong on this diagonal.} 11. O-O $6 {[%csl Rg4][%cal Gf6g4,Gd7g4] It is not good to castle too early, because from now on White will have to consider ...[Ng4] ideas.} O-O (11... Ng4 $5 {is already interesting.} 12. h3 Nh2 {Quite exotic, but works according to the engine. 🙂}) 12. d3 Bg4 {Forcing the queen to some awkward square.} 13. Qe3 Re8 $17 {[%csl Ya1,Yb1,Yc1,Gd6,Ge8,Gf6][%cal Ye4d3] Black is extremely active and has great chances to attack on the kingside, while White's pieces are just standing on the back rank.} *

