1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Bc4 Nf6 5. O-O {A very common move, but objectively speaking not really challenging if Black knows what to do against it. On the other hand, it is very safe for White, so finding a combative response wasn't easy here.} Nxe4 6. Re1 d5 {[%csl Ge4][%cal Gd5e4,Rd5c4]} 7. Bxd5 Qxd5 8. Nc3 $1 {[%cal Yd4c3,Rd1d5,Ye4c3,Re1e8] The point of the whole variation, Black can't take on [c3], because both the queen and the king are pinned. Black has a wide choice here, with almost all the queen moves being quite okay.} Qa5 ({This is the main line, and according to my analyses it is the one which can provide the most winning chances for Black. For example} 8... Qf5 {is also very safe for Black, but if White wants, they can make a draw there pretty effortlessly.}) 9. Nxe4 ({White has to take like this, the alternatives are much worse. For instance,} 9. Rxe4+ $2 Be6 10. Nxd4 O-O-O $1 {With a very unpleasant pin on the d-file!} 11. Be3 Nxd4 12. Rxd4 Ba3 $1 {Spectacular and strong!} 13. Qb1 Bd6 {⩱ And Black is clearly better with the very strong bishops!}) 9... Be6 {[%cal Ge8c8] Protecting the king from the discovered checks, and also preparing to play ... [O-O-O]. White has to react quickly, since otherwise Black is just up a pawn.} 10. Neg5 {[%cal Rg5e6] White is winning back the pawn on [e6].} O-O-O 11. Nxe6 fxe6 12. Rxe6 {So far we have been following the main line of the 5. [O-O] variation with still thousands of games played from this position, but now it is time to surprise our opponent.} Qh5 $5 ({Bringing the queen closer to White's king makes a lot of sense, since if we look at the main line,} 12... Bd6 13. Bg5 $1 {White isn't only developing the bishop with a tempo, but also blocks the queen's way to [h5].}) 13. Bg5 (13. Bf4 $4 {This logical developing move immediately gives up a lot of material.} Qf5 {-+}) 13... Rd5 {We don't have a choice, but fortunately the rook on [d5] is just fine. 🙂} 14. Qd3 {A tricky move, but it should eventually transpose to the 14. [Bh4] line.} Bd6 (14... Rxg5 $2 {Materially this looks very good for Black, but unfortunately we cannot finish development.} 15. Nxg5 Qxg5 16. Re8+ Kd7 17. Rae1 {± Black's king is very weak.}) 15. Bh4 g5 {Transposing to the main line.} *

