awn with a tempo, but the problem is that our usual way of protecting [c6] will also protect the pawn on [e6].🙂} Nb8 $1 {[%csl Gc6,Ge6][%cal Gb8c6,Gc8e6]} 11. Qg4 $2 {[%cal Rg4g7,Rg4e6] It is a double attack and a losing move. :} O-O 12. Nxe6 Bf6 $1 {This strong move was missed in both games which reached this position.} 13. Re1 Re8 14. f4 Qd6 15. f5 {White saves the knight, but will lose a pawn.} Bxe6 16. fxe6 Nd7 $19 {[%csl Re6][%cal Gd7e5,Gd7f8] After ...[Ne5] or ...[Nf8], White is losing material.} *

