[Nxb4] followed by ...[a5] and White can no longer chase away the knight with [a3].} 13. Bxd4 O-O 14. Be3 {White has the pair of bishops, but we have good counterplay against the [e4]-pawn and on the kingside.} Rae8 15. b5 Ne5 16. O-O h4 $1 17. Qe2 (17. g4 $4 {Would be already losing for White,} Nfxg4 $1 18. hxg4 h3 $1 19. Bxh3 Bxg4 20. Bxg4 Nxg4 {-+}) 17... Nh5 $132 {[%csl Rg3][%cal Rh5g3,Rh4g3]} ({With huge pressure on White's kingside. Note that} 17... hxg3 $2 {would be a big mistake due to} 18. f4 $1 {±}) *

