his move is not so awkward, since the bishop is already out on [e3].} Bxe3 {Not allowing White to spoil our structure on [b6].} 10. Qxe3 a3 $1 {This is an important move. If we delay playing ...[a3] then White could play [a3]! themselves, fixing our pawn on a light square. Then it would be much easier for White to attack the pawn.} 11. b3 Nf6 {[%cal Ge8g8]} 12. Bb5 O-O 13. Bxc6 $1 (13. O-O {Would allow} Nb4 $1 14. Rfc1 Qe7 {∞ And the knight on [b4] is very annoying.}) 13... bxc6 $132 {[%cal Gf8e8,Re8e4,Rf6e4,Yd6d5,Yc8f5] We will put pressure on the [e4]-pawn in the next moves by playing ...[Re8], ...[d5] and possibly even ...[Bf5].} *

