s, but the text looks good enough to me.}) 11. Bg5 {[%csl Rf6][%cal Gg5d8] This pin is something I would like to avoid in this line since it is not so easy to meet it. In this particular position White's queenside position is very awkward, and this gives a few good ways to address the pin.} h6 12. Bh4 g5 $1 {[%csl Ge8][%cal Ye8c8] We are weakening our kingside, but fortunately our king hasn't castled yet!} 13. Bg3 Qe7 {[%cal Re7e4,Rf6e4] Developing with tempo.} 14. f3 Be6 {Another tempo!} 15. N3d4 Nxd4 16. cxd4 (16. Nxd4 Bd7 {⇆ Black is castling long in the next move, with a very decent position.}) 16... Nh5 17. Bf2 d5 $15 {[%csl Re2,Rf1,Rf2][%cal Ge8c8] Black is slightly better, since White still has to solve a lot of issues with their development.} *

