1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 {This is the starting position of the Scotch Game. White gains space advantage in the centre, but in return they move their knight for a second time, which can lead to issues with development in some variations. Black's main goals are connected with the [e4]-pawn, either to challenge it with ...[f5] or ...[d5], or just put pressure on it by playing ...[Nf6], ...[Re8] and similar moves.} Bc5 5. Nb3 {Recently, this is White's most dangerous attempt against the Classical Variation. White removes the knight from the centre, but gains a tempo on the bishop, so time is not an issue. Since they do not have to defend the knight on [d4], White very often aims to play [Qe2] and [O-O-O], which can obviously make the game pretty sharp.} Bb6 ({This is the most natural square for the bishop. The more obscure options are} 5... Bb4+ {or 5...Be7 , but Black has difficulties according to current theory.}) 6. Nc3 Qf6 {[%cal Gg8e7,Gd7d6,Ye8c8,Yc8e6]} ({The third most popular move in the position behind} 6... Nf6 {and 6...d6 . The point is to develop with ...[Nge7] but first develop the queen to a more active square, which also makes ...[O-O-O] possible later. We also have a mate in one threat. 🙂 Obviously the main moves are fine as well, I just don't like the pin which can happen in the 6...Nf6 7.Bg5 lines.}) 7. Qe2 {[%csl Gf2][%cal Ge2f2,Gc3d5] By far the main move for White, protecting [f2], preparing to play [Nd5] and also [O-O-O] is one step closer.} Nge7 {[%csl Gd5][%cal Ye7d5] Continuing development and addressing the [Nd5] threat.} 8. Be3 {[%cal Ge1c1] By far the most common move in this position. White is continuing the development and preparing to castle long.} d6 {We are doing exactly the same!} 9. Nb5 {[%csl Yc7][%cal Rb5c7] Not very common to say the least, but it is good to know a few things about dangerous looking moves.} a6 $1 10. Bxb6 axb5 11. Bxc7 Qxb2 {This looks like a good trade for Black as White's queenside is very vulnerable now.} 12. Rd1 O-O 13. Bxd6 Re8 {[%csl Ya2,Re1,Re2][%cal Ye7f5,Ga8a2] Black has a lot of activity for the sacrificed pawn.} *

