hen why not?}) 11. Nxc7 Ra4 $5 (11... Qxb2 {This pretty much forces a draw.} 12. Nxa8 Nd4 $1 13. Nxd4 Qxa1+ 14. Qd1 Qc3+ 15. Qd2 {(15.Ke2 Qc5 ⩱ With ...[Be6] next Black is trapping the knight on [a8] with a better position. )} Qa1+) 12. c3 d5 {[%csl Re1][%cal Ra4e4] Opening the position against White's king in the centre.} 13. exd5 Qf4 {[%cal Ra4e4,Rf4c7]} 14. f3 $1 {White has to stop ...[Re4].} Qxc7 15. dxc6 Nf5 {[%csl Re1] With strong compensation for the pawns. The computer claims that it is possible to hold this position as White, but humans can't continue to play on a 3500 level for long.} *

