trong.}) 9. h3 {[%csl Gg4][%cal Gh3g4] Since the [b2]-pawn is hanging, [Ng4] was again a threat, which is addressed by this move.} O-O 10. Nc3 Re8 {Bringing the rook to the center and putting more pressure to the [e4]-pawn.} 11. Ne2 Be5 $132 {[%csl Rb2][%cal Ye5b2,Yd6d5,Ya7a5,Ya5a4,Yd7d5,Gc8a6] With equal chances. We can play ... [d5] or ...[d6], and pushing the a-pawn is also an idea. This not only gains some space on the queenside but prepares to trade the light-squared bishops with ... [Ba6].} *

