ms in the endgame, so 10...Ng4 looks like a pretty decent line.}) 11. Qf4 d6 {[%cal Yg7g5] We want to play ...[g5] and force the exchange of queens.} 12. f3 g5 13. Qg3 Qxg3 (13... Ne5 $5 {It is also interesting to allow White to double our pawns on the h-file.} 14. Qxh4 gxh4 15. f4 Nxd3 16. cxd3 f5 {⇆ With a very unusual pawn structure. The computer is claiming the Black is completely fine, but I would rather go with the text move. 🙂}) 14. hxg3 Ne5 15. g4 a5 $10 {[%csl Ge5] White is very solid, but it is not clear what their plan should be. Our knight on [e5] is very strong.} *

