way to break the pin.} 11. Nxa4 {[%cal Yc2c3,Rc3b4,Rd1a4] A nice tactical trick from White.} Re8 $1 {[%cal Rf6e4]} (11... Rxa4 $6 {Unfortunately this recapture is not good enough, because after} 12. c3 Ra8 13. cxb4 Nxb4 14. e5 {⩲ White has some slight pressure.}) 12. c3 (12. a3 Rxa4 13. c3 Ra8 14. cxb4 Nxb4 15. e5 Nxd3 16. Qxd3 Nh7 {We are going to play ...[b6]-...[Bb7] and then ...[Nf8], with a very solid position. If possible, we can even try to play ...[Re6]-[g6] once the bishop is already on the long diagonal.}) 12... Bf8 {[%csl Ra4] White's knight on [a4] is horrible, and coupled with a lead in development, Black will have full compensation for the pawn.} 13. Re1 d5 $1 14. exd5 (14. e5 $6 Ne4 {⩱ There are big problems with the [e5]-pawn.}) 14... Rxe1+ 15. Nxe1 Qxd5 {[%csl Ra4][%cal Gc8g4,Gc6e5] White is very passive and behind in development, Black at the very least has equal chances here.} *

