1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bc4 $6 {The Italian Four Knights, played in thousands and thousands of games, but it is simply a dubious move, allowing Black to equalise on the spot.} Nxe4 $1 {[%cal Yc3e4,Rd7d5,Rd5c4,Rd5e4] After this move it is rather White who has to be objectively careful to maintain the balance. White is losing their central pawn, while Black is keeping [e5].} 5. Nxe4 d5 {[%csl Ge5][%cal Rd5c4,Rd5e4] Taking back the material while having an extra pawn in the centre.} 6. Bd3 (6. Bxd5 $2 Qxd5 {Now it is not only the centre, but Black also have the pair of bishops.} 7. Nc3 {(7.d3 Bg4 8.h3 Bh5 9.g4 Bg6 10.Qe2 O-O-O ∓ )} Qa5 8. O-O Bg4 {∓}) 6... dxe4 7. Bxe4 {[%csl Ge5] The position is similar to the Scotch Four Knights 4. [d4] chapter, when with Black we had positions like this, and wanted to attack White's [e4]-pawn.} Bd6 {[%csl Ge5][%cal Gd6e5]} 8. O-O O-O 9. Re1 {[%cal Ye4c6,Yf7f5,Rf3e5,Re1e5] White is preventing ... [f5], by putting additional pressure to the [e5]-pawn.} (9. d3 $6 {White is not challenging our superiority in the centre.} Bg4 10. h3 Bh5 {⩱ Black is slightly better, and White has already count on ...[f5]-ideas.}) 9... Bg4 {[%csl Rd1,Yf3][%cal Yg4d1,Yf7f5] By pinning the knight ...[f5] is again very much a threat for White.} 10. c3 {[%cal Yf7f5,Rd1b3,Rb3g8] White is preventing ...[f5], aiming to meet it with a [Qb3]+ after taking on [c6], when they can take the pawn on [e5], but without weakening the kingside.} Kh8 {[%csl Gh8][%cal Yf7f5,Re5e4,Rb3g8] Stepping out of the [a2]-[g8] diagonal. Which means [Qb3] won't come with check anymore.} 11. h3 (11. Qb3 $2 {This is just bad now, because after} Na5 $1 {-+ Black's next move is ...[f5] with a huge attack.}) 11... Bh5 {[%cal Yh5d1,Rf7f5] We are keeping the pin and have no interest in giving up the strong bishop.} 12. Bxc6 {White goes for the pawn, but have already seen similar, Black will have great compensation.} bxc6 13. g4 Bg6 14. Nxe5 Qh4 {[%cal Rh4h3]} (14... Bxe5 $5 {Playing with opposite-coloured bishops also looks very tempting.} 15. Rxe5 f5 {⩱}) 15. Qf3 f5 {[%csl Gf8][%cal Rf5g4]} 16. Nxg6+ hxg6 {[%cal Rf5g4,Ga8e8] ...[fxg4] is a huge threat, but even ...[Rae8] is not easy for White to respond to.} *

