1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Nd5 {An odd move, but not a bad one at all. In the worst case for White, the game can transpose to the Belgrade Gambit, which is a playable opening.} Nxe4 {This seems like the easiest line for Black. As I said, 4. [Nd5] is fine, so the task is to look for something reliable and not so chaotic.} ({•} 4... Bc5 {Obviously a good move, but White has two moves that can lead to a quite messy game.} 5. Bc4 $5 {or 5.c3 Nxe4 6.d4 ∞ With some unclear lines.}) ({•} 4... Nxd5 {Of course, this move should be enough for equality, but Black is struggling a bit to get it and this is not necessary after 4. [Nd5].} 5. exd5 Nd4 6. Nxd4 exd4 7. Qg4 {White may have a small pressure if Black is not precise.}) 5. Qe2 {[%cal Re2e4,Yf3e5]} ({Much easier to handle than} 5. d4 {.}) 5... Nf6 $1 {[%cal Yf6d5] Since this line is pretty rare, it is much better to go for this line rather than the unclear option of 5...[f5].} (5... f5 6. d4 $1 {And things are getting very messy.} d6 {(6...exd4 7.Nd2 d3 8.Qf3 ∞ Computer supports Black, but the moves are not obvious. )} 7. Qc4 $1 {Making both ...[Be6] and ...[O-O] more difficult.} Be7 8. Be3 Be6 $1 {Again, the engine likes this, but it is unnecessary.} 9. Nxc7+ Qxc7 10. Qxe6 Qa5+ $1 11. c3 Nxc3 12. Bc4 Ne4+ 13. Kf1 Rf8 {⩱ Black is slightly better.}) 6. Nxe5 {White doesn't have a choice, this is the only way to win back the pawn.} Nd4 $1 {[%cal Rd4c2,Rd4e2,Rf6d5] Everything is under attack.} 7. Qc4 {[%csl Gc2,Gd5][%cal Yc4d5,Yc4c2]} Ne6 {[%csl Ge6,Gf6][%cal Yf6d5,Yc7c6] Black is completely safe.} 8. d4 $2 {Probably the most obvious move, but it is a mistake!} (8. Nxf6+ Qxf6 9. d4 Bd6 {Black is castling next, with at least an equal position.}) 8... b5 $1 {[%cal Ye6d4,Yf6d5] The queen has to protect both the [d5]-knight and the [d4]-pawn, and it is not possible now.} 9. Qxb5 c6 {[%cal Rc6b5,Rc6d5] Black is winning material.} 10. Nxc6 dxc6 11. Qxc6+ Bd7 12. Nxf6+ gxf6 $17 {[%csl Gd7,Ge6,Gf8] White only managed to get two pawns for the piece, which is obviously not enough.} *

