 natural move is even losing for Black.} 14. a4 $1 bxa4 15. Rxa4 {+-}) 14. f3 Qxe2+ 15. Kxe2 Bc4+ 16. Ke1 Bxd4 {[%csl Rf1] The rook can't go anywhere.} 17. fxe4 Bxf1 18. Kxf1 Rxa8 $17 {[%csl Gb5,Gb7,Gf7,Gg7,Gh7] Our pawn structure is ideal, the doubled-pawns are very good in defense, it will be tough for White to create a passed pawn on the queenside, while on the kingside Black can even target White's weaknesses first before pushing the pawns.} *

