e an attack here, and} 9. g5 {is met by} Nxe4 $1 10. dxe4 Qa5+ {∓ ( 9.a4 Nxg4 -+)}) 7... Ne8 {[%csl Gg5] White has completed their goal of playing [g5], but what is next? One pawn is not enough for an attack.} 8. Bc4 (8. Nxd4 exd4 9. Ne2 Bc5 {⩱ ...[c6] and ...[d5] are coming.}) 8... c6 {[%csl Rc4][%cal Yc6b5,Gb7b5,Ga7a5,Yd7d5] A very useful move, preparing both ...[b5], and once we move the bishop, ...[d5] as well.} 9. Nxd4 (9. h4 Bc7 $1 {∓ ...[d5] is next.}) 9... exd4 10. Ne2 Bc5 $15 {[%cal Gd7d5] With ...[d5] coming next, White only weakened their position and there was no attack at all.} *

