ck, one is obviously to push for ...[d5], and the other one is to gain the pair of bishops by playing ...[Na5]!} 7. Bg5 {White stops ...[d5] for the moment, but now we can go for the [c4]-bishop!} ({•} 7. c3 h6 {We will play ...[Bf8] next in order to avoid any [b4]-[b5] tempo, and then ...[d5].}) ({•} 7. a4 h6 8. Nc3 Nb4 {With the idea of ...[c6]-[d5], Black is doing very well.}) 7... h6 8. Bh4 Na5 $10 {[%cal Gg7g5,Ra5c4] Black is at the very least fine, once we are taking the light-squared bishop we can even break the pin by playing ...[g5], since the sacrifices are not dangerous anymore.} *

