n the next 5-10 moves nothing happens with that pawn, it can give us a space advantage in the center and better chances in the long run. From this moment a direct confrontation begins and we have to be very precise, but so does White!} 6. Bxd5 $2 {It is quite hard to believe, but the 3rd most common move OTB is this capture. White is giving up the very strong bishop and inviting our queen to protect the [e5]-pawn.} Qxd5 7. Nc3 Qd6 {[%csl Gd6,Ge5][%cal Gd6e5] The queen is well-placed on [d6]. Not only is it protecting the pawn, but we can also get very ambitious with ...[O-O-O].} 8. O-O Bf5 $17 {[%cal Ge8c8,Yf7f6,Yg7g5] We will castle long next, and then start attacking on the kingside.} *

