 is the usual route for the queen in this structure. It wants to reach the [g6]-square, and from there it can put pressure on the [e4]-knight, or, if that moves, the [c2]-pawn. It also helps with ...[Bh3] or ...[Bg4] ideas.} 13. Ne4 Qg6 14. c4 $6 {[%csl Yb6,Rd3,Rd4] White is trying to cut the [b6]-knight from the game, but not only it is not possible, it also weakens crucial square, like [d3] and [d4].} Bf5 15. Nbc3 Na4 $17 {[%cal Ra4c3] With the threat of ...[Nxc3], we can conclude that White's plan has failed regarding our knight.} *

