n both ways on the back rank, they have to give back some material.} 16. Bxc6 bxc6 17. Rxa7 Kb8 $1 {Of course this is needed, since White was threatening with [Ra8]+.} 18. Nc3 Kxa7 19. f3 (19. Nxd1 Bxd1 {-+ This is just losing for White, since we will collect the pawns on the queenside.}) 19... Rd2 20. fxg4 Rxb2 $15 {[%csl Rb4,Rc4] We are likely to get both pawns on the queenside, which makes our position preferable. Still, White definitely keeps decent chances to save the game.} *

