sl Ge4][%cal Gd3e4,Gh3g1,Gg1f3] White controls the [e4]-square, opens the diagonal for the bishop, and also prepares [Ng1]-[f3], since Black's ...[e4] is not dangerous anymore.} (10. O-O $4 g4 {-+}) 10... Qb6 ({(After 10 moves, we are already in unexplored territory 1 OTB game! Pretty much everyone plays)} 10... Bg7 {in this position, but keeping the option of playing with ...[g4] and then ...[Bc5] could become the new main line in one day. 🙂In any case, bringing the queen to attack on [f2] and [b2] can't be too bad.}) 11. Nc3 {White wants to develop and this move is also very useful against ...[Bc5], because of [Na4]-threats.} g4 12. Ng1 Bc5 {Although we are not losing material, in fact, we are regaining the pawn, we give up all the pressure in White's position and create weaknesses in our own.} 13. Na4 Bxf2+ 14. Kf1 Qd8 15. Kxf2 Qd4+ 16. Kf1 Qxa4 17. Qe1 $16 {[%csl Ra5,Rf6][%cal Ge2d1,Gg1e2,Ge1h4] We have a lot of weak squares, and our pieces are also pretty bad.} *

