definitely not doing anything.} 17. c4 {(17.Kf1 Ng4 -+ With ...[Nf2] or ... [Qf6] next, Black is winning. )} Bd4 {-+ Winning the rook on [a1].}) 15... Qe7 $1 {[%csl Ya5,Ge2] The [e2]-bishop is obviously much more valuable than the [a5]-knight.} 16. Bd3 (16. bxa5 Qxe2 17. Qxe2 Rxe2 {∓ Even though we are down a pawn for the moment, we'll surely win back the [a5]-pawn and then just be much better with the pair of bishops and more active pieces.}) 16... Qc7 $1 {[%csl Ya1,Yb1,Yc1] Just a nice illustrative line, that White's queenside doesn't matter at all.} 17. bxa5 Bg4 $19 {[%csl Gc7,Gd6,Ge8,Gf6,Gg4]} (17... Bg4 {It seems like that Black is up a piece or two, and the engine's -3 evaluation confirms that. One possible line is} 18. h3 Bc5+ 19. Kh1 Nh5 20. Bh7+ Kxh7 21. d4 Ng3+ 22. Kg1 Nxf1 23. hxg4 Ng3 24. dxc5 Rad8 {-+ And White's queenside is still yet to do anything.}) *

