d also gains a tempo, since Black doesn't really want to trade queens.} Qc7 12. Nc3 h6 13. Nge4 Nh7 $1 {∞ With ...[f5] and ...[e4] coming, Black's position is still much easier to play. ( • 11.d3?? loses a piece to 11...Bg4! 12.Qe3 Nd5 13.Qxe5 Bxe2 14.Qxe2 Bxg5 -+)}) 11... Nd5 $1 {[%cal Re7g5,Gf7f5,Ge5e4]} 12. Nh3 (12. Nge4 $2 {Giving additional tempi to Black.} f5 13. Ng3 e4 {-+ Black is already winning material.}) 12... Rb4 $15 {[%csl Yf3,Yh3][%cal Gb4h4,Yf7f5,Yg7g5] We can bring the rook to [h4] and then start pushing the kingside pawns.} *

