ly go to [c5] and target [f2].} 12. Na4 $6 {[%csl Gc5] White wants to force the bishop away from the diagonal.} Bxf2+ $1 13. Kxf2 Qd4+ {[%cal Rd4f2,Rd4a4]} 14. Ke1 Qxa4 ({Black could already make the draw, with} 14... Qe4+ 15. Kf2 Qd4+ {, but it is probably better not to do so, since only Black can be better.}) 15. d4 $1 {[%cal Gc1f4] This is the only move for White; they have to start developing.} c5 $40 {[%cal Gc8b7,Ra4d4] Opening up the long diagonal and also attacking on [d4]. White has to be careful here.} (15... c5 {One line which loses quickly goes} 16. dxe5 Nxg2+ $1 17. Bxg2 Qh4+ 18. Kf1 Ba6+ 19. Kg1 Rd8 {-+ and White didn't manage to finish the development.}) *

