the c-pawn. That centre would look nice, but it is also quite easy to attack, or undermine.} Be6 ({This is a new move. The theory is} 6... Bg4 {, which is also fine, but I see no reason to deviate from our usual moves, and also Black's main choice after} 7. h3 {is to take on [f3], which I don't like too much as I would prefer to keep the bishop pair.}) 7. d4 exd4 8. cxd4 O-O-O 9. Nc3 Ne7 $132 {[%csl Ga6,Gb7,Gc6,Gc7][%cal Yf7f5,Yh7h6,Yg7g5,Gc8b8] Our king is very safe on the queenside, and we can start pushing for ...[g5] and ...[f5] on the kingside.} *

