nce [Na3] would immediately threaten [Nc4], this seems like a step backward for White.} Ne7 {[%csl Ge5][%cal Ge7g6,Yg6e5] There are other good moves for Black, but developing and bringing the knight to [g6], where it is going to protect the pawn on [e5], looks pretty good.} 7. Nbd2 {[%cal Rd2c4]} Ng6 {[%csl Ge5][%cal Gg6e5] In time to protect on [e5].} 8. Nc4 Qe6 {[%csl Rc4][%cal Gd3d4,Ye6c4] Three queen moves are pretty much of equal value according to the computer, ...[Qf6], ...[Qe7] and this one, but I definitely like this the most, since it is preventing White from going [d4], and maybe we can go for ...[c5] in the next move.} 9. b3 {[%csl Gc4][%cal Yb3c4,Gd3d4] Protecting the knight and preparing to play [d4].} c5 {I see no problems with this move.} 10. Ne3 (10. Bb2 f6 {⩱ And if anything the bishop is misplaced on [b2].}) 10... Qc6 $132 {[%cal Gf7f6,Gc8e6,Ge8c8] With ...[f6], ...[Be6] and then long castle coming up, Black's position looks pretty good.} *

