 lines, because of the extra move [O-O], but as you will see it means pretty much nothing.} exd4 7. e5 $6 {[%cal Gc8f5,Gg8e7,Ge7f5,Ge7d5] Positionally speaking, a quite questionable move. It weakens light-squares and gives us the [f5] and [d5]-squares.} Qd5 8. Nxd4 {At least in this version of the endgame the rook is coming to [d1].} (8. Qxd4 Qxd4 9. Nxd4 c5 10. Ne2 Bf5 {⩱ With ... [O-O-O] next, Black is getting the d-file.}) 8... c5 9. Nf3 Qxd1 10. Rxd1 h6 $10 {[%cal Gc8d7,Ge8c8,Gg8e7,Ge7g6,Rg6e5,Yd7c6,Rc6f3] This is really a Berlin endgame. 🙂 The only difference is that Black can castle long, which changes the evaluation from White is trying to be better, to Black is playing for the advantage.} *

