 lines, because of the extra move [O-O], but as you will see it means pretty much nothing.} exd4 7. Qxd4 Qxd4 {Let's see what White can do with that extra tempo.} 8. Nxd4 Bd7 9. Be3 (9. Nc3 O-O-O {Will transpose either to 9. [Be3] or 9. [Bf4] lines once the bishop develops.}) 9... O-O-O 10. Nc3 (10. Nd2 c5 11. Ne2 Ne7 {⩱ And Black is better with ... [Nc6] and ...[h5]-[h4] to follow, since} 12. Bxc5 $4 {is losing material to} Bb5 {-+}) 10... Re8 {[%csl Re4][%cal Ge8e4] Do not change the winning ⩱ team!} 11. Rfe1 Ne7 12. Rad1 Ng6 13. f3 h5 $15 {[%cal Gb7b6,Gf7f6] So, as a conclusion, we can say that we have to do everything the same as against 5. [d4], and the 1 extra move for White is meaningless.} *

