 lines, because of the extra move [O-O], but as you will see it means pretty much nothing.} exd4 7. Nxd4 Bd7 $1 {[%csl Gd6][%cal Yc8d7,Ge8c8] This is what I like about ...[Qd6]! We can comfortably continue the development behind the queen.} 8. Be3 (8. Nc3 O-O-O {And White has nothing better than} 9. Be3 Nh6 {and we are transposing to 8. [Be3] [O-O-O] lines.}) 8... O-O-O 9. Nc3 Nh6 {[%csl Gh6][%cal Rh6g4,Yf7f5] The knight is great there, supporting ...[f5] and going towards [g4].} 10. f3 (10. h3 Qg6 11. Qf3 f6 {⩱ And Black is re-routing the knight with ...[Nf7]-[e5].}) 10... f5 $1 {The main idea is to open the position, but if White rejects it, there is also a positional point in this move.} 11. Qe2 f4 $1 12. Bf2 Nf7 $15 {[%cal Gd6f6,Gf7e5,Gf8d6,Yg7g5,Yh7h5,Yg5g4] The knight is going to [e5], and then we can start attacking on the kingside.} *

