cing the bishop to a worse square.} 13. Bc2 f5 $1 {Similar story, bishop pair vs better centre.} 14. Ng3 {[%csl Rf5]} (14. Ng5 {Not a much better square than [g3], since the knight will eventually be forced back to [h3].} e4 {First, the queen has to go back to a passive square.} 15. Qd1 Nf6 {∞ Black will complete development with ...[Bd6] and will send back the knight to [h3] by playing ...[h6].}) 14... g6 15. O-O Bg7 $132 {[%cal Ge8g8,Gc7c5,Ga5c6] With chances for both sides. I prefer Black though, since it is tough to find a clear plan for White. It is also easier to play with the more space.} *

