Rf1 {[%cal Rf4f5]} Bh7 {So [f4]-[f5] doesn't come with tempo.} 27. h3 Nd3 28. Qe3 (28. Qf3 a5 {∓ Not so easy to make moves for White, but at least the material is equal for now.}) 28... Bxe4 $1 {Black is winning a pawn.} 29. Nxe4 Nxe5 $1 {[%cal Rd4d1]} 30. Nc3 (30. Rxd4 $2 cxd4 {-+}) 30... Nc6 31. Qxe7 Nxe7 $17 {[%csl Yc5,Yc7] Black has the extra pawn; converting it is not so easy, though.} 32. Rde1 Kf8 33. f5 f6 34. g4 Rd3 35. Ne2 Nd5 36. Rd1 Nf4 37. Nxf4 Rxd1 38. Ne6+ Ke8 39. Nxd8 Rxf1+ 40. Kxf1 Kxd8 41. Ke2 Kd7 42. Kd3 h5 43. gxh5 Kc6 44. Kc4 Kd6 45. a4 Ke5 0-1

