1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bb5 Bd6 5. d3 O-O 6. a3 Nd4 7. Bc4 c6 8. Ba2 Bc7 9. h3 Ne6 10. Bxe6 $6 {White is trying to close the diagonals for Black's bishops for a while but can't really make use of it.} (10. O-O Re8 11. Re1 h6 {but not 10...d5 11.exd5 Nxd5 12.Re1}) 10... fxe6 $1 {[%cal Gf8f2] Of course, opening the f-file for the rook.} 11. Bg5 Qe8 12. Bxf6 {White is giving up the other bishop as well, but the knights don't really have good squares, and even if it needs some time, the bishops will come into play.} Rxf6 13. Ne2 d6 14. Ng3 Bd7 15. O-O Qg6 {Black is slowly improving, while it is not clear what White should do.} 16. Nh2 $6 (16. b4 {Probably this was something to try. It is not proactive; the goal is simply to have [c5] at some moment when the bishop could go to [b6].} Raf8 17. c4 h5 {⩱ Black is, of course, better, but it is not easy to play ...[Bb6] because of [c5].}) 16... Raf8 17. Qe2 Bb6 {[%csl Gb6][%cal Rb6f2] One of the bishops is already great!} 18. Nh1 {[%csl Yh1,Yh2] The knights are not so great!} (18. Ng4 Rf4 {∓}) 18... Be8 {[%cal Ge8h5] Black wants to bring the bishop to [h5] later.} 19. g3 $2 {Blundering a pawn, but the position was already difficult.} Bxf2+ $1 20. Kg2 (20. Nxf2 Qxg3+ 21. Kh1 Rxf2 {-+}) (20. Rxf2 Rxf2 21. Nxf2 Qxg3+ {+ -+}) 20... Bb6 {Black easily won with the extra pawn.} 21. Rf3 Rxf3 22. Nxf3 Qh6 23. Rf1 Bh5 24. g4 Be8 25. Qd2 Be3 26. Qb4 Bc5 27. Qxb7 Qe3 28. d4 exd4 29. Qe7 d3 30. Ng3 dxc2 31. Nd4 Rxf1 32. Qxe6+ Kf8 0-1

