1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nge7 5. O-O Ng6 6. c3 d5 7. exd5 Qxd5 8. d4 Bg4 9. Bxc6+ $2 {This is a bad move, but White had an interesting follow-up.} Qxc6 10. Nxe5 {An interesting way of grabbing a pawn.} Nxe5 11. Qe1 O-O-O (11... f6 $1 {This is much easier than what I played. Basically White can't really keep the extra pawn in this variation.} 12. dxe5 O-O-O 13. Nd2 Re8 {Black is taking back the pawn and having the advantage of the bishop pair.} 14. Qe4 Qxe4 15. Nxe4 Rxe5 {⩱}) {13.exf6 (This move will mean an open g-file, and a very dangerous attack from Black. Over -3) 13...Re8 14.Qd2 gxf6 -+ 14.Be3 Bh3! 15.gxh3 gxf6 16.f3 Rxe3 -+ is a nice line from the engine.} 12. Qxe5 Bd6 (12... h5 $1 {It was better to start with this, so [Qg5] will never be a tempo.}) 13. Qg5 h5 {Black has great compensation for the pawn.} 14. Qd2 $4 ({Most likely this move was supposed to be} 14. Nd2 {, but strange things can happen in online games. 🙂}) 14... Rde8 (14... h4 $1 15. f3 h3 $1 16. fxg4 Bxh2+ {+ -+ or 15.h3 Bxh3 16.gxh3 Rh6 -+}) 15. f3 Bf5 16. Na3 h4 17. Nc2 h3 18. g3 Bxg3 19. hxg3 h2+ 20. Kh1 Bxc2 $4 (20... Qb5 {-+}) 21. Qxc2 Qxf3+ 22. Qg2 Qd3 23. Bf4 Re2 24. Rf2 Rhe8 25. Raf1 Rxf2 26. Qxf2 Qe4+ 27. Qg2 Qd3 28. Kxh2 Re2 29. Rf2 Re1 30. Qh3+ Kb8 31. Rg2 (31. Qh8+ Ka7 32. Bxc7 {+-}) 31... Qf1 $19 32. g4 1-0

