1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. d3 d5 5. exd5 Nxd5 6. O-O Nb6 7. Bb5 Bd6 8. Re1 f6 9. d4 O-O 10. Bxc6 bxc6 11. dxe5 fxe5 12. Bg5 Qe8 13. Nbd2 Qg6 {So far, everything is pretty normal, and here White played an unusual move.} 14. c4 $6 {[%csl Ge5][%cal Rb6d5,Yc4d5,Yc4c5,Gg5h4,Gh4g3,Rf3e5] White prevents the knight from joining via [d5], but more importantly, [c5] is an option, especially after the bishop reaches [g3].} c5 {[%cal Gc8b7,Rb7g2] A quite obvious move for Black; there is no [c5] for White, and the long diagonal is opened.} (14... Bg4 {This also looks very good, but White has} 15. Nxe5 $1 {and it is apparently fine for them.} Bxe5 16. Qxg4 Rf5 17. Nf3 Bxb2 18. Rab1 Bc3 19. Rec1 Bf6 20. h4 h6 {Maybe Black is winning a piece?} 21. Qe4 $1 {Not quite!} Bxg5 22. hxg5 Re8 {∞ but not 21...hxg5?? 22.g4 +-}) 15. b3 $2 {White has no time to protect pawns on the queenside when there is attack on the kingside.} (15. Bh4 {The bishop should go to [g3] and protect the king.} Bb7 16. Bg3 e4 17. Nh4 Qe6 {⇆ The knight on [h4] is quite weird.}) 15... Bb7 {[%csl Rg5][%cal Ge5e4] The bishop is hanging on [g5] since Black can take twice on [f3]. Also, ...[e4] is a threat now.} 16. Qb1 $1 {This was the only try, and it worked out in the game.} (16. Bh4 e4 17. Ng5 Rae8 {-+ Black is completely winning since White was not in time to bring the bishop to [g3].}) 16... e4 $2 (16... Qh5 $1 {would have given Black a great advantage, with the same plan as the move before: take twice on [f3], and the bishop is hanging on [g5].} 17. Qd3 Bxf3 18. Nxf3 Rxf3 19. Qxf3 Qxg5 {-+ The computer recommends 17.Re4! , but White obviously doesn't have nearly enough for the exchange. 17...Bxe4 18.Nxe4 h6 ∓}) 17. Nxe4 Rxf3 $4 {Just doesn't work.} 18. Nxd6 $1 (18. gxf3 $4 Bxe4 19. Qxe4 Qxg5+ {+ -+}) 18... Qxd6 (18... Qxg5 19. Nxb7 Raf8 20. Re2 {+- Black has no attack, and the knight on [b6] is worse than the one on [b7].}) 19. gxf3 $18 {[%csl Rb6] Black doesn't have enough pieces to attack, especially since the knight on [b6] is horrible.} Rf8 20. Be7 Qf4 21. Re3 Rf5 22. Qd1 h6 23. Qd8+ Kh7 24. Qd3 Kh8 25. Qd8+ Kh7 26. Qd3 Nc8 27. Bxc5 h5 28. b4 h4 29. Re4 Bxe4 30. Qxe4 Qxe4 31. fxe4 Rf3 32. Rd1 Nb6 33. Bxb6 cxb6 34. Kg2 Rc3 35. Rd4 h3+ 36. Kf1 Rc2 37. a3 Rc3 38. a4 Ra3 39. c5 Rxa4 40. c6 b5 41. Rd5 Ra1+ 42. Ke2 Rc1 43. Rc5 1-0

